parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS/VSA module can cause the vehicle's ABS and VSA systems to malfunction, leading to loss of braking power, increased stopping distances, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: The ABS
VSA
and traction control lights illuminate on the dashboard
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking
and the vehicle may pull to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of the rear brake pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake pads wear out quickly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking
and the rear brake pads need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the brake pedal can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal vibrates or shakes when braking
the vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking
and the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag does not deploy in an accident
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the passenger airbag is on
the driver side airbag has not been replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incomplete or inadequate repair of recalled airbag components can lead to continued safety risks, including airbag failure or unexpected deployment.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is still illuminated after recall repair
the airbag system is not functioning properly after repair
the dealer is unable to fix the problem
the repair is not completed correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Recall Notification or Information
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to receive recall notification or inadequate information can lead to continued safety risks, as owners may not be aware of the need for repair.
symptoms: No recall notification received
unclear or incomplete information about the recall
difficulty in determining if the vehicle is included in the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
requiring frequent oil changes
and may exhibit signs of oil burning or leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the VTC actuator can cause the engine to rattle or make a grinding noise, which can lead to premature engine wear and potentially cause engine failure, resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine rattles or makes a grinding noise
especially during cold start-up
and may be accompanied by a check engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fouled spark plugs can cause the engine to misfire, leading to reduced engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially cause engine failure, resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine misfires
and the check engine light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences problems shifting gears
and the transmission may slip or hesitate.
